The paper is about salient object detection in video sequences using 3D convolutional neural networks. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper proposes a novel approach using 3D convolutional neural networks, which involves designing and training a network to learn spatiotemporal features from video sequences. This suggests that the paper may also fall under sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
